DESCRIPTION:One of the best improvisers on the stand-up circuit grapples wi
 th the overwhelming chaos of the world. Sometimes there's just too much stu
 ff to process. Join Ben as he does the comedy equivalent of reading an ency
 clopedia cover to cover and squeezes the comedy juice out of everything und
 er the sun\, from genetics to tattoos\, XL bullies to board games and beyon
 d. It'll be a bit like watching Wikipedia having a nervous breakdown. For f
 ans of Ross Noble\, Jason Byrne and heroic nonsense. "Displays a crackling\
 , spontaneous energy in which we're swept up." (Fest) "An accomplished comi
 c." (Time Out) "Perfect... the audience were hysterical." (Huffington Post)
